    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in original, unmolested configuration. The heart of this chassis is a 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine that exhibits exceptional compression across all rotor faces, indicative of meticulous thermal management and maintenance. The complex vacuum-actuated boost control system operates flawlessly, providing a linear power delivery through the five-speed manual gearbox and Torsen limited-slip differential. The suspension retains its factory double-wishbone geometry with no bushing degradation or hydraulic leaks. This vehicle is a definitive example of 90s JDM engineering, featuring a pristine interior with no typical UV damage to the dash or plastics, and a chassis that remains structurally perfect with zero oxidation.",
